#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md
msgid "Yii3 is not an incremental upgrade from Yii 1.1. Yii 2.0 was a full rewrite, and Yii3 changes the architecture again: Composer packages, namespaces, PHP 8, PSR interfaces, dependency injection, explicit routes, middleware, and separate packages for features that were built into the framework in Yii 1.1."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md
msgid "Treat this as building a new Yii3 application with the benefit of Yii 1.1 experience. Reuse the domain knowledge, database schema, user workflows, and selected code after refactoring. Do not try to reproduce the Yii 1.1 application structure in Yii3. A direct search-and-replace conversion is not realistic."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md
msgid "For additional background, read the Yii 2.0 guide section [Upgrading from Version 1.1](https://www.yiiframework.com/doc/guide/2.0/en/intro-upgrade-from-v1). It explains the first major break from Yii 1.1: Composer, namespaces, object configuration, view changes, controller return values, widgets, assets, helpers, forms, query builder, Active Record, and URL management. Yii3 builds on many of those changes and makes dependencies more explicit."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Recommended approach"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md
msgid "Choose one of these paths:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md
msgid "Build a new Yii3 application directly when the Yii 1.1 application is small or you are already rewriting request flows."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md
msgid "Move Yii 1.1 concepts to Yii 2.0 first when the team needs a smaller conceptual step."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md
msgid "Keep Yii 1.1 running and rebuild critical flows in Yii3 one by one."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md
msgid "For most long-lived applications, the third option is the least risky. Create a Yii3 application, connect it to the same database, and build vertical slices: route, action, input validation, persistence, view, assets, and tests.  Each slice should be idiomatic Yii3, even when it is based on behavior from the Yii 1.1 application."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "Scale the application"
msgid "Prepare the Yii 1.1 application"
msgstr "扩展应用程序"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md
msgid "Useful preparation can happen before the Yii3 application is ready. These refactorings make old behavior easier to understand and reduce the amount of Yii 1.1 framework state that crosses into the new code:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md
msgid "Remove direct `Yii::app()` access from reusable code where practical. If a full refactoring is too large, keep `Yii::app()` calls near controllers, widgets, and commands, then pass values and services to lower-level code explicitly."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md
msgid "Introduce repositories or query services for database reads currently spread across controllers, views, `CActiveRecord` methods, and widgets. Yii3 can use Active Record, but it does not require it for every persistence task."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md
msgid "Separate business rules from framework infrastructure. Code that does not extend `CComponent`, read global application state, or render views is easier to reuse as a specification for Yii3 code."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md
msgid "Move reusable behavior out of large controllers and Active Record classes into Yii 1.1 application components or plain services. Yii3 services are configured and injected differently, but the responsibility boundary is similar."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md
msgid "Add tests or characterization checks around routes and workflows you plan to rebuild first. They become the executable specification for the Yii3 slice."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "For example, instead of reading post archive data directly from several controllers or widgets, create a small service that describes the application need:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"class PostRepository extends CComponent\n"
"{\n"
"    public function getArchive()\n"
"    {\n"
"        // ...\n"
"    }\n"
"\n"
"    public function getTopForFrontPage($limit = 10)\n"
"    {\n"
"        // ...\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md
msgid "The Yii3 implementation may use `yiisoft/active-record`, `yiisoft/db`, or another persistence layer. The important point is that controllers and views no longer need to know that detail."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Things to learn before starting"
msgstr "需要学习的内容"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md
msgid "Some Yii3 application-template choices are likely to be new in a Yii 1.1 codebase:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md
msgid "[Composer](https://getcomposer.org/). Yii3 applications and packages are installed through Composer and loaded with PSR-4 autoloading."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md
msgid "[Namespaces](https://www.php.net/manual/en/language.namespaces.php). Yii3 classes are namespaced instead of using Yii 1.1-style class prefixes and path aliases for class loading."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "[Docker](https://www.docker.com/get-started/). The default Yii3 application template includes Docker configuration.  Using it gives each application its own repeatable environment and reduces differences between local development and production."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "[Environment variables](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Environment_variable). Yii3 templates commonly use them for environment-specific settings and secrets, especially in Docker-based deployments. This follows the same idea as [12-factor app configuration](https://12factor.net/config)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "[Actions](../structure/action.md). Yii3 does not require controller inheritance. A route can point to any callable, and the default template uses invokable action classes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v1.md
msgid "[Application structure](../structure/overview.md). Yii3's default structure is different from Yii 1.1. Start with the Yii3 template and change it only when the application needs it."
msgstr ""

